TITLE: La Città Ideale
ATTRIBUTION: Anonymous. Most likely attributed to Laurana, Luciano
DESCRIPTION: The famous Ideal City of Urbino, attribution uncertain.
SUBJECTS: Urban landscape, architecture, perspective, Renaissance ideals, symmetry.
CONTENT: The painting depicts an idealized Renaissance city with perfectly proportioned buildings, harmonious streets, and balanced perspectives, symbolizing order, rationality, and the pursuit of architectural perfection.
